1/*
2 * It is strictly recommended to include "testlib.h" before any other include
3 * in your code. In this case testlib overrides compiler specific "random()".
4 *
5 * If you can't compile your code and compiler outputs something about
6 * ambiguous call of "random_shuffle", "rand" or "srand" it means that
7 * you shouldn't use them. Use "shuffle", and "rnd.next()" instead of them
8 * because these calls produce stable result for any C++ compiler. Read
9 * sample generator sources for clarification.
10 *
11 * Please read the documentation for class "random_t" and use "rnd" instance in
12 * generators. Probably, these sample calls will be useful for you:
13 * rnd.next(); rnd.next(100); rnd.next(1, 2);
14 * rnd.next(3.14); rnd.next("[a-z]{1,100}").
15 *
16 * Also read about wnext() to generate off-center random distribution.
17 *
18 * See https://github.com/MikeMirzayanov/testlib/ to get latest version or bug tracker.
19 */

44/* NOTE: This file contains testlib library for C++.
45 *
46 * Check, using testlib running format:
47 * check.exe <Input_File> <Output_File> <Answer_File> [<Result_File> [-appes]],
48 * If result file is specified it will contain results.
49 *
50 * Validator, using testlib running format:
51 * validator.exe < input.txt,
52 * It will return non-zero exit code and writes message to standard output.
53 *
54 * Generator, using testlib running format:
55 * gen.exe [parameter-1] [parameter-2] [... paramerter-n]
56 * You can write generated test(s) into standard output or into the file(s).
57 *
58 * Interactor, using testlib running format:
59 * interactor.exe <Input_File> <Output_File> [<Answer_File> [<Result_File> [-appes]]],
60 * Reads test from inf (mapped to args[1]), writes result to tout (mapped to argv[2],
61 * can be judged by checker later), reads program output from ouf (mapped to stdin),
62 * writes output to program via stdout (use cout, printf, etc).
63 */

392static bool __testlib_prelimIsNaN(double r) {
393 volatile double ra = r;
394#ifndef __BORLANDC__
395 return ((ra != ra) == true) && ((ra == ra) == false) && ((1.0 > ra) == false) && ((1.0 < ra) == false);
396#else
397 return std::_isnan(ra);
398#endif
399}

404static std::string removeDoubleTrailingZeroes(std::string value) {
405 while (!value.empty() && value[value.length() - 1] == '0' && value.find('.') != std::string::npos)
406 value = value.substr(0, value.length() - 1);
407 if (!value.empty() && value[value.length() - 1] == '.')
408 return value + '0';
409 else
410 return value;

451static bool __testlib_isNaN(double r) {
452 __TESTLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(double) == sizeof(long long));
453 volatile double ra = r;
454 long long llr1, llr2;
455 std::memcpy((void *) &llr1, (void *) &ra, sizeof(double));
456 ra = -ra;
457 std::memcpy((void *) &llr2, (void *) &ra, sizeof(double));
458 long long llnan = 0xFFF8000000000000LL;
459 return __testlib_prelimIsNaN(r) || llnan == llr1 || llnan == llr2;
460}
461
462static double __testlib_nan() {
463 __TESTLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(double) == sizeof(long long));
464#ifndef NAN
465 long long llnan = 0xFFF8000000000000LL;
466 double nan;
467 std::memcpy(&nan, &llnan, sizeof(double));
468 return nan;
469#else
470 return NAN;
471#endif
472}

474static bool __testlib_isInfinite(double r) {
475 volatile double ra = r;
476 return (ra > 1E300 || ra < -1E300);
477}

479#ifdef __GNUC__
480__attribute__((const))
481#endif
482inline bool doubleCompare(double expected, double result, double MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR) {
483 MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR += 1E-15;
484 if (__testlib_isNaN(expected)) {
485 return __testlib_isNaN(result);
486 } else if (__testlib_isInfinite(expected)) {
487 if (expected > 0) {
488 return result > 0 && __testlib_isInfinite(result);
489 } else {
490 return result < 0 && __testlib_isInfinite(result);
491 }
492 } else if (__testlib_isNaN(result) || __testlib_isInfinite(result)) {
493 return false;
494 } else if (__testlib_abs(result - expected) <= MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR) {
495 return true;
496 } else {
497 double minv = __testlib_min(expected * (1.0 - MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR),
498 expected * (1.0 + MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR));
499 double maxv = __testlib_max(expected * (1.0 - MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR),
500 expected * (1.0 + MAX_DOUBLE_ERROR));
501 return result >= minv && result <= maxv;
502 }
503}
504
505#ifdef __GNUC__
506__attribute__((const))
507#endif
508inline double doubleDelta(double expected, double result) {
509 double absolute = __testlib_abs(result - expected);
510
511 if (__testlib_abs(expected) > 1E-9) {
512 double relative = __testlib_abs(absolute / expected);
513 return __testlib_min(absolute, relative);
514 } else
515 return absolute;
516}

521#ifdef ON_WINDOWS

565#if __cplusplus > 199711L || defined(_MSC_VER)
566template<typename T>
567#ifdef __GNUC__
568__attribute__((const))
569#endif
570static std::string vtos(const T &t, std::true_type) {
571 if (t == 0)
572 return "0";
573 else {
574 T n(t);
575 bool negative = n < 0;
576 std::string s;
577 while (n != 0) {
578 T digit = n % 10;
579 if (digit < 0)
580 digit = -digit;
581 s += char('0' + digit);
582 n /= 10;
583 }
584 std::reverse(s.begin(), s.end());
585 return negative ? "-" + s : s;
586 }
587}
588
589template<typename T>
590static std::string vtos(const T &t, std::false_type) {
591 std::string s;
592 static std::stringstream ss;
593 ss.str(std::string());
594 ss.clear();
595 ss << t;
596 ss >> s;
597 return s;
598}

600template<typename T>
601static std::string vtos(const T &t) {
602 return vtos(t, std::is_integral<T>());
603}
604
605/* signed case. */
606template<typename T>
607static std::string toHumanReadableString(const T &n, std::false_type) {
608 if (n == 0)
609 return vtos(n);
610 int trailingZeroCount = 0;
611 T n_ = n;
612 while (n_ % 10 == 0)
613 n_ /= 10, trailingZeroCount++;
614 if (trailingZeroCount >= 7) {
615 if (n_ == 1)
616 return "10^" + vtos(trailingZeroCount);
617 else if (n_ == -1)
618 return "-10^" + vtos(trailingZeroCount);
619 else
620 return vtos(n_) + "*10^" + vtos(trailingZeroCount);
621 } else
622 return vtos(n);
623}
624
625/* unsigned case. */
626template<typename T>
627static std::string toHumanReadableString(const T &n, std::true_type) {
628 if (n == 0)
629 return vtos(n);
630 int trailingZeroCount = 0;
631 T n_ = n;
632 while (n_ % 10 == 0)
633 n_ /= 10, trailingZeroCount++;
634 if (trailingZeroCount >= 7) {
635 if (n_ == 1)
636 return "10^" + vtos(trailingZeroCount);
637 else
638 return vtos(n_) + "*10^" + vtos(trailingZeroCount);
639 } else
640 return vtos(n);
641}

643template<typename T>
644static std::string toHumanReadableString(const T &n) {
645 return toHumanReadableString(n, std::is_unsigned<T>());
646}
647#else

649static std::string vtos(const T& t)
650{
651 std::string s;

653 ss.str(std::string());
654 ss.clear();
655 ss << t;
656 ss >> s;
657 return s;
658}

662 return vtos(n);
663}

676/*
677 * Very simple regex-like pattern.
678 * It used for two purposes: validation and generation.
679 *
680 * For example, pattern("[a-z]{1,5}").next(rnd) will return
681 * random string from lowercase latin letters with length
682 * from 1 to 5. It is easier to call rnd.next("[a-z]{1,5}")
683 * for the same effect.
684 *
685 * Another samples:
686 * "mike|john" will generate (match) "mike" or "john";
687 * "-?[1-9][0-9]{0,3}" will generate (match) non-zero integers from -9999 to 9999;
688 * "id-([ac]|b{2})" will generate (match) "id-a", "id-bb", "id-c";
689 * "[^0-9]*" will match sequences (empty or non-empty) without digits, you can't
690 * use it for generations.
691 *
692 * You can't use pattern for generation if it contains meta-symbol '*'. Also it
693 * is not recommended to use it for char-sets with meta-symbol '^' like [^a-z].
694 *
695 * For matching very simple greedy algorithm is used. For example, pattern
696 * "[0-9]?1" will not match "1", because of greedy nature of matching.
697 * Alternations (meta-symbols "|") are processed with brute-force algorithm, so
698 * do not use many alternations in one expression.
699 *
700 * If you want to use one expression many times it is better to compile it into
701 * a single pattern like "pattern p("[a-z]+")". Later you can use
702 * "p.matches(std::string s)" or "p.next(random_t& rd)" to check matching or generate
703 * new string by pattern.
704 *
705 * Simpler way to read token and check it for pattern matching is "inf.readToken("[a-z]+")".
706 *
707 * All spaces are ignored in regex, unless escaped with \. For example, ouf.readLine("NO SOLUTION")
708 * will expect "NOSOLUTION", the correct call should be ouf.readLine("NO\\ SOLUTION") or
709 * ouf.readLine(R"(NO\ SOLUTION)") if you prefer raw string literals from C++11.
710 */
711class random_t;
712
713class pattern {
714public:
715 /* Create pattern instance by string. */
716 pattern(std::string s);
717
718 /* Generate new string by pattern and given random_t. */
719 std::string next(random_t &rnd) const;
720
721 /* Checks if given string match the pattern. */
722 bool matches(const std::string &s) const;
723
724 /* Returns source string of the pattern. */
725 std::string src() const;
726
727private:
728 bool matches(const std::string &s, size_t pos) const;
729
730 std::string s;
731 std::vector<pattern> children;
732 std::vector<char> chars;
733 int from;
734 int to;
735};

737/*
738 * Use random_t instances to generate random values. It is preferred
739 * way to use randoms instead of rand() function or self-written
740 * randoms.
741 *
742 * Testlib defines global variable "rnd" of random_t class.
743 * Use registerGen(argc, argv, 1) to setup random_t seed be command
744 * line (to use latest random generator version).
745 *
746 * Random generates uniformly distributed values if another strategy is
747 * not specified explicitly.
748 */
749class random_t {
750private:
751 unsigned long long seed;
752 static const unsigned long long multiplier;
753 static const unsigned long long addend;
754 static const unsigned long long mask;
755 static const int lim;
756
757 long long nextBits(int bits) {
758 if (bits <= 48) {
759 seed = (seed * multiplier + addend) & mask;
760 return (long long) (seed >> (48 - bits));
761 } else {
762 if (bits > 63)
763 __testlib_fail("random_t::nextBits(int bits): n must be less than 64");
764
765 int lowerBitCount = (random_t::version == 0 ? 31 : 32);
766
767 long long left = (nextBits(31) << 32);
768 long long right = nextBits(lowerBitCount);
769
770 return left ^ right;
771 }
772 }
773
774public:
775 static int version;
776
777 /* New random_t with fixed seed. */
778 random_t()
779 : seed(3905348978240129619LL) {
780 }
781
782 /* Sets seed by command line. */
783 void setSeed(int argc, char *argv[]) {
784 random_t p;
785
786 seed = 3905348978240129619LL;
787 for (int i = 1; i < argc; i++) {
788 std::size_t le = std::strlen(argv[i]);
789 for (std::size_t j = 0; j < le; j++)
790 seed = seed * multiplier + (unsigned int) (argv[i][j]) + addend;
791 seed += multiplier / addend;
792 }
793
794 seed = seed & mask;
795 }
796
797 /* Sets seed by given value. */
798 void setSeed(long long _seed) {
799 seed = (unsigned long long) _seed;
800 seed = (seed ^ multiplier) & mask;
801 }

820 /* Random value in range [0, n-1]. */
821 int next(int n) {
822 if (n <= 0)
823 __testlib_fail("random_t::next(int n): n must be positive");
824
825 if ((n & -n) == n) // n is a power of 2
826 return (int) ((n * (long long) nextBits(31)) >> 31);
827
828 const long long limit = INT_MAX / n * n;
829
830 long long bits;
831 do {
832 bits = nextBits(31);
833 } while (bits >= limit);
834
835 return int(bits % n);
836 }
837
838 /* Random value in range [0, n-1]. */
839 unsigned int next(unsigned int n) {
840 if (n >= INT_MAX)
841 __testlib_fail("random_t::next(unsigned int n): n must be less INT_MAX");
842 return (unsigned int) next(int(n));
843 }
844
845 /* Random value in range [0, n-1]. */
846 long long next(long long n) {
847 if (n <= 0)
848 __testlib_fail("random_t::next(long long n): n must be positive");
849
850 const long long limit = __TESTLIB_LONGLONG_MAX / n * n;
851
852 long long bits;
853 do {
854 bits = nextBits(63);
855 } while (bits >= limit);
856
857 return bits % n;
858 }

965 /*
966 * Weighted next. If type == 0 than it is usual "next()".
967 *
968 * If type = 1, than it returns "max(next(), next())"
969 * (the number of "max" functions equals to "type").
970 *
971 * If type < 0, than "max" function replaces with "min".
972 */
973 int wnext(int n, int type) {
974 if (n <= 0)
975 __testlib_fail("random_t::wnext(int n, int type): n must be positive");
976
977 if (abs(type) < random_t::lim) {
978 int result = next(n);
979
980 for (int i = 0; i < +type; i++)
981 result = __testlib_max(result, next(n));
982
983 for (int i = 0; i < -type; i++)
984 result = __testlib_min(result, next(n));
985
986 return result;
987 } else {
988 double p;
989
990 if (type > 0)
991 p = std::pow(next() + 0.0, 1.0 / (type + 1));
992 else
993 p = 1 - std::pow(next() + 0.0, 1.0 / (-type + 1));
994
995 return __testlib_crop((int) (double(n) * p), 0, n);
996 }
997 }
998
999 /* See wnext(int, int). It uses the same algorithms. */
1000 long long wnext(long long n, int type) {
1001 if (n <= 0)
1002 __testlib_fail("random_t::wnext(long long n, int type): n must be positive");
1003
1004 if (abs(type) < random_t::lim) {
1005 long long result = next(n);
1006
1007 for (int i = 0; i < +type; i++)
1008 result = __testlib_max(result, next(n));
1009
1010 for (int i = 0; i < -type; i++)
1011 result = __testlib_min(result, next(n));
1012
1013 return result;
1014 } else {
1015 double p;
1016
1017 if (type > 0)
1018 p = std::pow(next() + 0.0, 1.0 / (type + 1));
1019 else
1020 p = 1 - std::pow(next() + 0.0, 1.0 / (-type + 1));
1021
1022 return __testlib_crop((long long) (double(n) * p), 0LL, n);
1023 }
1024 }

1026 /* Returns value in [0, n). See wnext(int, int). It uses the same algorithms. */
1027 double wnext(double n, int type) {
1028 if (n <= 0)
1029 __testlib_fail("random_t::wnext(double n, int type): n must be positive");
1030
1031 if (abs(type) < random_t::lim) {

1039

1041 } else {

1046 else
1047 p = 1 - std::pow(next() + 0.0, 1.0 / (-type + 1));
1048
1049 return __testlib_crop(n * p, 0.0, n);
1050 }
1051 }

1159 /* Returns random permutation of the given size (values are between `first` and `first`+size-1)*/
1160 template<typename T, typename E>
1161 std::vector<E> perm(T size, E first) {
1162 if (size < 0)
1163 __testlib_fail("random_t::perm(T size, E first = 0): size must non-negative");
1164 else if (size == 0)
1165 return std::vector<E>();
1166 std::vector<E> p(size);
1167 E current = first;
1168 for (T i = 0; i < size; i++)
1169 p[i] = current++;
1170 if (size > 1)
1171 for (T i = 1; i < size; i++)
1172 std::swap(p[i], p[next(i + 1)]);
1173 return p;
1174 }

1176 /* Returns random permutation of the given size (values are between 0 and size-1)*/
1177 template<typename T>
1178 std::vector<T> perm(T size) {
1179 return perm(size, T(0));
1180 }

1182 /* Returns `size` unordered (unsorted) distinct numbers between `from` and `to`. */
1183 template<typename T>
1184 std::vector<T> distinct(int size, T from, T to) {
1185 std::vector<T> result;
1186 if (size == 0)
1187 return result;
1188
1189 if (from > to)
1190 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct expected from <= to");
1191
1192 if (size < 0)
1193 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct expected size >= 0");
1194
1195 uint64_t n = to - from + 1;
1196 if (uint64_t(size) > n)
1197 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct expected size <= to - from + 1");
1198
1199 double expected = 0.0;
1200 for (int i = 1; i <= size; i++)
1201 expected += double(n) / double(n - i + 1);
1202
1203 if (expected < double(n)) {
1204 std::set<T> vals;
1205 while (int(vals.size()) < size) {
1206 T x = T(next(from, to));
1207 if (vals.insert(x).second)
1208 result.push_back(x);
1209 }
1210 } else {
1211 if (n > 1000000000)
1212 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct here expected to - from + 1 <= 1000000000");
1213 std::vector<T> p(perm(int(n), from));
1214 result.insert(result.end(), p.begin(), p.begin() + size);
1215 }
1216
1217 return result;
1218 }
1219
1220 /* Returns `size` unordered (unsorted) distinct numbers between `0` and `upper`-1. */
1221 template<typename T>
1222 std::vector<T> distinct(int size, T upper) {
1223 if (size < 0)
1224 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct expected size >= 0");
1225 if (size == 0)
1226 return std::vector<T>();
1227
1228 if (upper <= 0)
1229 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct expected upper > 0");
1230 if (size > upper)
1231 __testlib_fail("random_t::distinct expected size <= upper");
1232
1233 return distinct(size, T(0), upper - 1);
1234 }
1235
1236 /* Returns random (unsorted) partition which is a representation of sum as a sum of integers not less than min_part. */
1237 template<typename T>
1238 std::vector<T> partition(int size, T sum, T min_part) {
1239 if (size < 0)
1240 __testlib_fail("random_t::partition: size < 0");
1241 if (size == 0 && sum != 0)
1242 __testlib_fail("random_t::partition: size == 0 && sum != 0");
1243 if (min_part * size > sum)
1244 __testlib_fail("random_t::partition: min_part * size > sum");
1245 if (size == 0 && sum == 0)
1246 return std::vector<T>();
1247
1248 T sum_ = sum;
1249 sum -= min_part * size;
1250
1251 std::vector<T> septums(size);
1252 std::vector<T> d = distinct(size - 1, T(1), T(sum + size - 1));
1253 for (int i = 0; i + 1 < size; i++)
1254 septums[i + 1] = d[i];
1255 sort(septums.begin(), septums.end());
1256
1257 std::vector<T> result(size);
1258 for (int i = 0; i + 1 < size; i++)
1259 result[i] = septums[i + 1] - septums[i] - 1;
1260 result[size - 1] = sum + size - 1 - septums.back();
1261
1262 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < result.size(); i++)
1263 result[i] += min_part;
1264
1265 T result_sum = 0;
1266 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < result.size(); i++)
1267 result_sum += result[i];
1268 if (result_sum != sum_)
1269 __testlib_fail("random_t::partition: partition sum is expected to be the given sum");
1270
1271 if (*std::min_element(result.begin(), result.end()) < min_part)
1272 __testlib_fail("random_t::partition: partition min is expected to be no less than the given min_part");
1273
1274 if (int(result.size()) != size || result.size() != (size_t) size)
1275 __testlib_fail("random_t::partition: partition size is expected to be equal to the given size");
1276
1277 return result;
1278 }
1279
1280 /* Returns random (unsorted) partition which is a representation of sum as a sum of positive integers. */
1281 template<typename T>
1282 std::vector<T> partition(int size, T sum) {
1283 return partition(size, sum, T(1));
1284 }
1285};

1291int random_t::version = -1;

1296}

1298static bool __pattern_isSlash(const std::string &s, size_t pos) {
1299 return s[pos] == '\\';
1300}
1301
1302#ifdef __GNUC__
1303__attribute__((pure))
1304#endif
1305static bool __pattern_isCommandChar(const std::string &s, size_t pos, char value) {
1306 if (pos >= s.length())
1307 return false;
1308
1309 int slashes = 0;
1310
1311 int before = int(pos) - 1;
1312 while (before >= 0 && s[before] == '\\')
1313 before--, slashes++;
1314
1315 return slashes % 2 == 0 && s[pos] == value;
1316}
1317
1318static char __pattern_getChar(const std::string &s, size_t &pos) {
1319 if (__pattern_isSlash(s, pos))
1320 pos += 2;
1321 else
1322 pos++;
1323
1324 return s[pos - 1];
1325}
1326
1327#ifdef __GNUC__
1328__attribute__((pure))
1329#endif
1330static int __pattern_greedyMatch(const std::string &s, size_t pos, const std::vector<char> chars) {
1331 int result = 0;
1332
1333 while (pos < s.length()) {
1334 char c = s[pos++];
1335 if (!std::binary_search(chars.begin(), chars.end(), c))
1336 break;
1337 else
1338 result++;
1339 }
1340
1341 return result;
1342}

1344std::string pattern::src() const {
1345 return s;
1346}
1347
1348bool pattern::matches(const std::string &s, size_t pos) const {
1349 std::string result;
1350
1351 if (to > 0) {
1352 int size = __pattern_greedyMatch(s, pos, chars);
1353 if (size < from)
1354 return false;
1355 if (size > to)
1356 size = to;
1357 pos += size;
1358 }
1359
1360 if (children.size() > 0) {
1361 for (size_t child = 0; child < children.size(); child++)
1362 if (children[child].matches(s, pos))
1363 return true;
1364 return false;
1365 } else
1366 return pos == s.length();
1367}

1369std::string pattern::next(random_t &rnd) const {
1370 std::string result;
1371 result.reserve(20);
1372
1373 if (to == INT_MAX)
1374 __testlib_fail("pattern::next(random_t& rnd): can't process character '*' for generation");
1375
1376 if (to > 0) {
1377 int count = rnd.next(to - from + 1) + from;
1378 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
1379 result += chars[rnd.next(int(chars.size()))];
1380 }
1381
1382 if (children.size() > 0) {
1383 int child = rnd.next(int(children.size()));
1384 result += children[child].next(rnd);
1385 }
1386
1387 return result;
1388}
1389
1390static void __pattern_scanCounts(const std::string &s, size_t &pos, int &from, int &to) {
1391 if (pos >= s.length()) {
1392 from = to = 1;
1393 return;
1394 }
1395
1396 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '{')) {
1397 std::vector<std::string> parts;
1398 std::string part;
1399
1400 pos++;
1401
1402 while (pos < s.length() && !__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '}')) {
1403 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, ','))
1404 parts.push_back(part), part = "", pos++;
1405 else
1406 part += __pattern_getChar(s, pos);
1407 }
1408
1409 if (part != "")
1410 parts.push_back(part);
1411
1412 if (!__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '}'))
1413 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1414
1415 pos++;
1416
1417 if (parts.size() < 1 || parts.size() > 2)
1418 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1419
1420 std::vector<int> numbers;
1421
1422 for (size_t i = 0; i < parts.size(); i++) {
1423 if (parts[i].length() == 0)
1424 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1425 int number;
1426 if (std::sscanf(parts[i].c_str(), "%d", &number) != 1)
1427 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1428 numbers.push_back(number);
1429 }
1430
1431 if (numbers.size() == 1)
1432 from = to = numbers[0];
1433 else
1434 from = numbers[0], to = numbers[1];
1435
1436 if (from > to)
1437 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1438 } else {
1439 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '?')) {
1440 from = 0, to = 1, pos++;
1441 return;
1442 }
1443
1444 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '*')) {
1445 from = 0, to = INT_MAX, pos++;
1446 return;
1447 }
1448
1449 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '+')) {
1450 from = 1, to = INT_MAX, pos++;
1451 return;
1452 }
1453
1454 from = to = 1;
1455 }
1456}
1457
1458static std::vector<char> __pattern_scanCharSet(const std::string &s, size_t &pos) {
1459 if (pos >= s.length())
1460 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1461
1462 std::vector<char> result;
1463
1464 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '[')) {
1465 pos++;
1466 bool negative = __pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '^');
1467 if (negative)
1468 pos++;
1469
1470 char prev = 0;
1471
1472 while (pos < s.length() && !__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, ']')) {
1473 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, '-') && prev != 0) {
1474 pos++;
1475
1476 if (pos + 1 == s.length() || __pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, ']')) {
1477 result.push_back(prev);
1478 prev = '-';
1479 continue;
1480 }
1481
1482 char next = __pattern_getChar(s, pos);
1483 if (prev > next)
1484 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1485
1486 for (char c = prev; c != next; c++)
1487 result.push_back(c);
1488 result.push_back(next);
1489
1490 prev = 0;
1491 } else {
1492 if (prev != 0)
1493 result.push_back(prev);
1494 prev = __pattern_getChar(s, pos);
1495 }
1496 }
1497
1498 if (prev != 0)
1499 result.push_back(prev);
1500
1501 if (!__pattern_isCommandChar(s, pos, ']'))
1502 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1503
1504 pos++;
1505
1506 if (negative) {
1507 std::sort(result.begin(), result.end());
1508 std::vector<char> actuals;
1509 for (int code = 0; code < 255; code++) {
1510 char c = char(code);
1511 if (!std::binary_search(result.begin(), result.end(), c))
1512 actuals.push_back(c);
1513 }
1514 result = actuals;
1515 }
1516
1517 std::sort(result.begin(), result.end());
1518 } else
1519 result.push_back(__pattern_getChar(s, pos));
1520
1521 return result;
1522}
1523
1524pattern::pattern(std::string s) : s(s), from(0), to(0) {
1525 std::string t;
1526 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
1527 if (!__pattern_isCommandChar(s, i, ' '))
1528 t += s[i];
1529 s = t;
1530
1531 int opened = 0;
1532 int firstClose = -1;
1533 std::vector<int> seps;
1534
1535 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
1536 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, i, '(')) {
1537 opened++;
1538 continue;
1539 }
1540
1541 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, i, ')')) {
1542 opened--;
1543 if (opened == 0 && firstClose == -1)
1544 firstClose = int(i);
1545 continue;
1546 }
1547
1548 if (opened < 0)
1549 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1550
1551 if (__pattern_isCommandChar(s, i, '|') && opened == 0)
1552 seps.push_back(int(i));
1553 }
1554
1555 if (opened != 0)
1556 __testlib_fail("pattern: Illegal pattern (or part) \"" + s + "\"");
1557
1558 if (seps.size() == 0 && firstClose + 1 == (int) s.length()
1559 && __pattern_isCommandChar(s, 0, '(') && __pattern_isCommandChar(s, s.length() - 1, ')')) {
1560 children.push_back(pattern(s.substr(1, s.length() - 2)));
1561 } else {
1562 if (seps.size() > 0) {
1563 seps.push_back(int(s.length()));
1564 int last = 0;
1565
1566 for (size_t i = 0; i < seps.size(); i++) {
1567 children.push_back(pattern(s.substr(last, seps[i] - last)));
1568 last = seps[i] + 1;
1569 }
1570 } else {
1571 size_t pos = 0;
1572 chars = __pattern_scanCharSet(s, pos);
1573 __pattern_scanCounts(s, pos, from, to);
1574 if (pos < s.length())
1575 children.push_back(pattern(s.substr(pos)));
1576 }
1577 }
1578}

1593inline bool isBlanks(C c) {
1594 return (c == LF || c == CR || c == SPACE || c == TAB);
1595}

1597inline std::string trim(const std::string &s) {
1598 if (s.empty())
1599 return s;
1600
1601 int left = 0;
1602 while (left < int(s.length()) && isBlanks(s[left]))
1603 left++;
1604 if (left >= int(s.length()))
1605 return "";
1606
1607 int right = int(s.length()) - 1;
1608 while (right >= 0 && isBlanks(s[right]))
1609 right--;
1610 if (right < 0)
1611 return "";
1612
1613 return s.substr(left, right - left + 1);
1614}

1754class FileInputStreamReader : public InputStreamReader {
1755private:
1756 std::FILE *file;
1757 std::string name;
1758 int line;

1760 std::vector<int> readChars;
1761 std::vector<int> undoReadChars;
1762
1763 inline int postprocessGetc(int getcResult) {
1764 if (getcResult != EOF)
1765 return getcResult;
1766 else
1767 return EOFC;
1768 }
1769
1770 int getc(FILE *file) {
1771 int c;
1772 int rc;
1773
1774 if (undoChars.empty()) {
1775 c = rc = ::getc(file);
1776 } else {
1777 c = undoChars.back();
1778 undoChars.pop_back();
1779 rc = undoReadChars.back();
1780 undoReadChars.pop_back();
1781 }
1782
1783 if (c == LF)
1784 line++;
1785
1786 readChars.push_back(rc);
1787 return c;
1788 }
1789
1790 int ungetc(int c/*, FILE* file*/) {
1791 if (!readChars.empty()) {
1792 undoReadChars.push_back(readChars.back());
1793 readChars.pop_back();
1794 }
1795 if (c == LF)
1796 line--;
1797 undoChars.push_back(c);
1798 return c;
1799 }

1801public:
1802 FileInputStreamReader(std::FILE *file, const std::string &name) : file(file), name(name), line(1) {
1803 // No operations.
1804 }

1807 if (testCase < 0 || testCase > __TESTLIB_MAX_TEST_CASE)
1808 __testlib_fail(format("testCase expected fit in [1,%d], but %d doesn't", __TESTLIB_MAX_TEST_CASE, testCase));
1809 readChars.push_back(testCase + 256);
1810 }
1811
1812 std::vector<int> getReadChars() {
1813 return readChars;
1814 }
1815
1816 int curChar() {
1817 if (feof(file))
1818 return EOFC;
1819 else {
1820 int c = getc(file);
1821 ungetc(c/*, file*/);
1822 return postprocessGetc(c);
1823 }
1824 }
1825
1826 int nextChar() {
1827 if (feof(file))
1828 return EOFC;
1829 else
1830 return postprocessGetc(getc(file));
1831 }
1832
1833 void skipChar() {
1834 getc(file);
1835 }
1836
1837 void unreadChar(int c) {
1838 ungetc(c/*, file*/);
1839 }

1842 return name;
1843 }
1844

1846 return line;
1847 }
1848

1851 return true;
1852 else {

1854 if (c == EOFC || (c == EOF && feof(file)))
1855 return true;

1858 }

1869class BufferedFileInputStreamReader : public InputStreamReader {
1870private:
1871 static const size_t BUFFER_SIZE;
1872 static const size_t MAX_UNREAD_COUNT;
1873
1874 std::FILE *file;
1875 std::string name;
1876 int line;
1877
1878 char *buffer;
1879 bool *isEof;
1880 int bufferPos;
1881 size_t bufferSize;
1882
1883 bool refill() {
1884 if (NULL == file)
1885 __testlib_fail("BufferedFileInputStreamReader: file == NULL (" + getName() + ")");
1886
1887 if (bufferPos >= int(bufferSize)) {
1888 size_t readSize = fread(
1889 buffer + MAX_UNREAD_COUNT,
1890 1,
1891 BUFFER_SIZE - MAX_UNREAD_COUNT,
1892 file
1893 );
1894
1895 if (readSize < BUFFER_SIZE - MAX_UNREAD_COUNT
1896 && ferror(file))
1897 __testlib_fail("BufferedFileInputStreamReader: unable to read (" + getName() + ")");
1898
1899 bufferSize = MAX_UNREAD_COUNT + readSize;
1900 bufferPos = int(MAX_UNREAD_COUNT);
1901 std::memset(isEof + MAX_UNREAD_COUNT, 0, sizeof(isEof[0]) * readSize);
1902
1903 return readSize > 0;
1904 } else
1905 return true;
1906 }
1907
1908 char increment() {
1909 char c;
1910 if ((c = buffer[bufferPos++]) == LF)
1911 line++;
1912 return c;
1913 }

1915public:

1920 bufferPos = int(MAX_UNREAD_COUNT);
1921 }

1927 }

1944 return EOFC;
1945
1946 return isEof[bufferPos] ? EOFC : buffer[bufferPos];
1947 }
1948

1950 if (!refill())
1951 return EOFC;
1952
1953 return isEof[bufferPos] ? EOFC : increment();
1954 }

1957 increment();
1958 }

1960 void unreadChar(int c) {
1961 bufferPos--;
1962 if (bufferPos < 0)
1963 __testlib_fail("BufferedFileInputStreamReader::unreadChar(int): bufferPos < 0");
1964 isEof[bufferPos] = (c == EOFC);
1965 buffer[bufferPos] = char(c);
1966 if (c == LF)
1967 line--;
1968 }

1971 return name;
1972 }

1984 fclose(file);
1985 file = NULL;

2384struct ValidatorBoundsHit {
2385 static const double EPS;
2386 bool minHit;
2387 bool maxHit;
2388
2389 ValidatorBoundsHit(bool minHit = false, bool maxHit = false) : minHit(minHit), maxHit(maxHit) {
2390 };
2391
2392 ValidatorBoundsHit merge(const ValidatorBoundsHit &validatorBoundsHit, bool ignoreMinBound, bool ignoreMaxBound) {
2393 return ValidatorBoundsHit(
2394 __testlib_max(minHit, validatorBoundsHit.minHit) || ignoreMinBound,
2395 __testlib_max(maxHit, validatorBoundsHit.maxHit) || ignoreMaxBound
2396 );
2397 }
2398};

2400struct ConstantBound {
2401 std::string value;
2402 bool broken;
2403
2404 template<typename T>
2405 void adjust(T t) {
2406 std::string t_string = std::to_string(t);
2407 if (t_string.length() >= 32) {
2408 broken = true;
2409 value = "";
2410 } else {
2411 if (!broken && value.empty())
2412 value = t_string;
2413 if (!broken && value != t_string) {
2414 broken = true;
2415 value = "";
2416 }
2417 }
2418 }
2419
2420 bool has_value() {
2421 return !value.empty() && !broken && value.length() < 32;
2422 }
2423};
2424
2425struct ConstantBounds {
2426 ConstantBound lowerBound;
2427 ConstantBound upperBound;
2428};
2429

2527 std::string prepVariableName(const std::string &variableName) {
2528 if (variableName.length() >= 2 && variableName != "~~") {
2529 if (variableName[0] == '~' && variableName.back() != '~')
2530 return variableName.substr(1);
2531 if (variableName[0] != '~' && variableName.back() == '~')
2532 return variableName.substr(0, variableName.length() - 1);
2533 if (variableName[0] == '~' && variableName.back() == '~')
2534 return variableName.substr(1, variableName.length() - 2);
2535 }
2536 return variableName;
2537 }
2538
2539 bool ignoreMinBound(const std::string &variableName) {
2540 return variableName.length() >= 2 && variableName != "~~" && variableName[0] == '~';
2541 }
2542
2543 bool ignoreMaxBound(const std::string &variableName) {
2544 return variableName.length() >= 2 && variableName != "~~" && variableName.back() == '~';
2545 }
2546
2547 void addBoundsHit(const std::string &variableName, ValidatorBoundsHit boundsHit) {
2548 if (isVariableNameBoundsAnalyzable(variableName)
2549 && _boundsHitByVariableName.size() < VALIDATOR_MAX_VARIABLE_COUNT) {
2550 std::string preparedVariableName = prepVariableName(variableName);
2551 _boundsHitByVariableName[preparedVariableName] = boundsHit.merge(_boundsHitByVariableName[preparedVariableName],
2552 ignoreMinBound(variableName), ignoreMaxBound(variableName));
2553 }
2554 }
2555
2556 void addVariable(const std::string &variableName) {
2557 if (isVariableNameBoundsAnalyzable(variableName)
2558 && _variables.size() < VALIDATOR_MAX_VARIABLE_COUNT) {
2559 std::string preparedVariableName = prepVariableName(variableName);
2560 _variables.insert(preparedVariableName);
2561 }
2562 }

2658 void writeTestMarkup() {
2659 if (!_testMarkupFileName.empty()) {
2660 std::vector<int> readChars = inf.getReadChars();
2661 if (!readChars.empty()) {
2662 std::string markup(TEST_MARKUP_HEADER);
2663 for (size_t i = 0; i < readChars.size(); i++) {
2664 int c = readChars[i];
2665 if (i + 1 == readChars.size() && c == -1)
2666 continue;
2667 if (c <= 256) {
2668 char cc = char(c);
2669 if (cc == '\\' || cc == '!')
2670 markup += '\\';
2671 markup += cc;
2672 } else {
2673 markup += TEST_CASE_OPEN_TAG;
2674 markup += toString(c - 256);
2675 markup += TEST_CASE_CLOSE_TAG;
2676 }
2677 }
2678 FILE* f;
2679 bool standard_file = false;
2680 if (_testMarkupFileName == "stdout")
2681 f = stdout, standard_file = true;
2682 else if (_testMarkupFileName == "stderr")
2683 f = stderr, standard_file = true;
2684 else {
2685 f = fopen(_testMarkupFileName.c_str(), "wb");
2686 if (NULL == f)
2687 __testlib_fail("Validator::writeTestMarkup: can't write test markup to (" + _testMarkupFileName + ")");
2688 }
2689 std::fprintf(f, "%s", markup.c_str());
2690 std::fflush(f);
2691 if (!standard_file)
2692 if (std::fclose(f))
2693 __testlib_fail("Validator::writeTestMarkup: can't close test markup file (" + _testCaseFileName + ")");
2694 }
2695 }

2697
2698 void writeTestCase() {
2699 if (_testCase > 0) {
2700 std::vector<int> readChars = inf.getReadChars();
2701 if (!readChars.empty()) {
2702 std::string content, testCaseContent;
2703 bool matchedTestCase = false;
2704 for (size_t i = 0; i < readChars.size(); i++) {
2705 int c = readChars[i];
2706 if (i + 1 == readChars.size() && c == -1)
2707 continue;
2708 if (c <= 256)
2709 content += char(c);
2710 else {
2711 if (matchedTestCase) {
2712 testCaseContent = content;
2713 matchedTestCase = false;
2714 }
2715 content = "";
2716 int testCase = c - 256;
2717 if (testCase == _testCase)
2718 matchedTestCase = true;
2719 }
2720 }
2721 if (matchedTestCase)
2722 testCaseContent = content;
2723
2724 if (!testCaseContent.empty()) {
2725 FILE* f;
2726 bool standard_file = false;
2727 if (_testCaseFileName.empty() || _testCaseFileName == "stdout")
2728 f = stdout, standard_file = true;
2729 else if (_testCaseFileName == "stderr")
2730 f = stderr, standard_file = true;
2731 else {
2732 f = fopen(_testCaseFileName.c_str(), "wb");
2733 if (NULL == f)
2734 __testlib_fail("Validator::writeTestCase: can't write test case to (" + _testCaseFileName + ")");
2735 }
2736 std::fprintf(f, "%s", testCaseContent.c_str());
2737 std::fflush(f);
2738 if (!standard_file)
2739 if (std::fclose(f))
2740 __testlib_fail("Validator::writeTestCase: can't close test case file (" + _testCaseFileName + ")");
2741 }
2742 }
2743 }
2744 }

2795 __testlib_fail("Call register-function in the first line of the main (registerTestlibCmd or other similar)");

2799 validator.writeTestOverviewLog();
2800 validator.writeTestMarkup();
2801 validator.writeTestCase();
2802 }
2803 }

2987static std::string __testlib_appendMessage(const std::string &message, const std::string &extra) {
2988 int openPos = -1, closePos = -1;
2989 for (size_t i = 0; i < message.length(); i++) {
2990 if (message[i] == InStream::OPEN_BRACKET) {
2991 if (openPos == -1)
2992 openPos = int(i);
2993 else
2994 openPos = INT_MAX;
2995 }
2996 if (message[i] == InStream::CLOSE_BRACKET) {
2997 if (closePos == -1)
2998 closePos = int(i);
2999 else
3000 closePos = INT_MAX;
3001 }
3002 }
3003 if (openPos != -1 && openPos != INT_MAX
3004 && closePos != -1 && closePos != INT_MAX
3005 && openPos < closePos) {
3006 size_t index = message.find(extra, openPos);
3007 if (index == std::string::npos || int(index) >= closePos) {
3008 std::string result(message);
3009 result.insert(closePos, ", " + extra);
3010 return result;
3011 }
3012 return message;
3013 }
3014
3015 return message + " " + InStream::OPEN_BRACKET + extra + InStream::CLOSE_BRACKET;
3016}

3018static std::string __testlib_toPrintableMessage(const std::string &message) {

3020 for (size_t i = 0; i < message.length(); i++) {
3021 if (message[i] == InStream::OPEN_BRACKET) {
3022 if (openPos == -1)
3023 openPos = int(i);
3024 else
3025 openPos = INT_MAX;

3027 if (message[i] == InStream::CLOSE_BRACKET) {
3028 if (closePos == -1)
3029 closePos = int(i);
3030 else
3031 closePos = INT_MAX;

3035 && closePos != -1 && closePos != INT_MAX
3036 && openPos < closePos) {

3046NORETURN void InStream::quit(TResult result, const char *msg) {
3047 if (TestlibFinalizeGuard::alive)
3048 testlibFinalizeGuard.quitCount++;
3049
3050 std::string message(msg);
3051 message = trim(message);
3052
3053 if (__testlib_hasTestCase) {
3054 if (result != _ok)
3055 message = __testlib_appendMessage(message, "test case " + vtos(__testlib_testCase));
3056 else {
3057 if (__testlib_testCase == 1)
3058 message = __testlib_appendMessage(message, vtos(__testlib_testCase) + " test case");
3059 else
3060 message = __testlib_appendMessage(message, vtos(__testlib_testCase) + " test cases");
3061 }
3062 }
3063
3064 // You can change maxMessageLength.
3065 // Example: 'inf.maxMessageLength = 1024 * 1024;'.
3066 if (message.length() > maxMessageLength) {
3067 std::string warn = "message length exceeds " + vtos(maxMessageLength)
3068 + ", the message is truncated: ";
3069 message = warn + message.substr(0, maxMessageLength - warn.length());
3070 }
3071
3072#ifndef ENABLE_UNEXPECTED_EOF
3073 if (result == _unexpected_eof)
3074 result = _pe;
3075#endif
3076
3077 if (testlibMode == _scorer && result != _fail)
3078 quits(_fail, "Scorer should return points only. Don't use a quit function.");
3079
3080 if (mode != _output && result != _fail) {
3081 if (mode == _input && testlibMode == _validator && lastLine != -1)
3082 quits(_fail, __testlib_appendMessage(__testlib_appendMessage(message, name), "line " + vtos(lastLine)));
3083 else
3084 quits(_fail, __testlib_appendMessage(message, name));
3085 }
3086
3087 std::FILE *resultFile;
3088 std::string errorName;
3089
3090 if (__testlib_shouldCheckDirt(result)) {
3091 if (testlibMode != _interactor && !ouf.seekEof())
3092 quit(_dirt, "Extra information in the output file");
3093 }
3094
3095 int pctype = result - _partially;
3096 bool isPartial = false;
3097
3098 switch (result) {
3099 case _ok:
3100 errorName = "ok ";
3101 quitscrS(LightGreen, errorName);
3102 break;
3103 case _wa:
3104 errorName = "wrong answer ";
3105 quitscrS(LightRed, errorName);
3106 break;
3107 case _pe:
3108 errorName = "wrong output format ";
3109 quitscrS(LightRed, errorName);
3110 break;
3111 case _fail:
3112 errorName = "FAIL ";
3113 quitscrS(LightRed, errorName);
3114 break;
3115 case _dirt:
3116 errorName = "wrong output format ";
3117 quitscrS(LightCyan, errorName);
3118 result = _pe;
3119 break;
3120 case _points:
3121 errorName = "points ";
3122 quitscrS(LightYellow, errorName);
3123 break;
3124 case _unexpected_eof:
3125 errorName = "unexpected eof ";
3126 quitscrS(LightCyan, errorName);
3127 break;
3128 default:
3129 if (result >= _partially) {
3130 errorName = format("partially correct (%d) ", pctype);
3131 isPartial = true;
3132 quitscrS(LightYellow, errorName);
3133 } else
3134 quit(_fail, "What is the code ??? ");
3135 }
3136
3137 if (resultName != "") {
3138 resultFile = std::fopen(resultName.c_str(), "w");
3139 if (resultFile == NULL) {
3140 resultName = "";
3141 quit(_fail, "Can not write to the result file");
3142 }
3143 if (appesMode) {
3144 std::fprintf(resultFile, "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"%s\"?>", appesModeEncoding.c_str());
3145 if (isPartial)
3146 std::fprintf(resultFile, "<result outcome = \"%s\" pctype = \"%d\">",
3147 outcomes[(int) _partially].c_str(), pctype);
3148 else {
3149 if (result != _points)
3150 std::fprintf(resultFile, "<result outcome = \"%s\">", outcomes[(int) result].c_str());
3151 else {
3152 if (__testlib_points == std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity())
3153 quit(_fail, "Expected points, but infinity found");
3154 std::string stringPoints = removeDoubleTrailingZeroes(format("%.10f", __testlib_points));
3155 std::fprintf(resultFile, "<result outcome = \"%s\" points = \"%s\">",
3156 outcomes[(int) result].c_str(), stringPoints.c_str());
3157 }
3158 }
3159 xmlSafeWrite(resultFile, __testlib_toPrintableMessage(message).c_str());
3160 std::fprintf(resultFile, "</result>\n");
3161 } else
3162 std::fprintf(resultFile, "%s", __testlib_toPrintableMessage(message).c_str());
3163 if (NULL == resultFile || fclose(resultFile) != 0) {
3164 resultName = "";
3165 quit(_fail, "Can not write to the result file");
3166 }
3167 }
3168
3169 quitscr(LightGray, __testlib_toPrintableMessage(message).c_str());
3170 std::fprintf(stderr, "\n");
3171
3172 inf.close();
3173 ouf.close();
3174 ans.close();
3175 if (tout.is_open())
3176 tout.close();
3177
3178 textColor(LightGray);
3179
3180 if (resultName != "")
3181 std::fprintf(stderr, "See file to check exit message\n");
3182
3183 halt(resultExitCode(result));
3184}

3208void InStream::xmlSafeWrite(std::FILE *file, const char *msg) {
3209 size_t lmsg = strlen(msg);
3210 for (size_t i = 0; i < lmsg; i++) {
3211 if (msg[i] == '&') {
3212 std::fprintf(file, "%s", "&amp;");
3213 continue;
3214 }
3215 if (msg[i] == '<') {
3216 std::fprintf(file, "%s", "&lt;");
3217 continue;
3218 }
3219 if (msg[i] == '>') {
3220 std::fprintf(file, "%s", "&gt;");
3221 continue;
3222 }
3223 if (msg[i] == '"') {
3224 std::fprintf(file, "%s", "&quot;");
3225 continue;
3226 }
3227 if (0 <= msg[i] && msg[i] <= 31) {
3228 std::fprintf(file, "%c", '.');
3229 continue;
3230 }
3231 std::fprintf(file, "%c", msg[i]);
3232 }

3560#ifdef __GNUC__
3561__attribute__((pure))
3562#endif
3563static inline bool equals(long long integer, const char *s) {
3564 if (integer == LLONG_MIN)
3565 return strcmp(s, "-9223372036854775808") == 0;
3566
3567 if (integer == 0LL)
3568 return strcmp(s, "0") == 0;
3569
3570 size_t length = strlen(s);
3571
3572 if (length == 0)
3573 return false;
3574
3575 if (integer < 0 && s[0] != '-')
3576 return false;
3577
3578 if (integer < 0)
3579 s++, length--, integer = -integer;
3580
3581 if (length == 0)
3582 return false;
3583
3584 while (integer > 0) {
3585 int digit = int(integer % 10);
3586
3587 if (s[length - 1] != '0' + digit)
3588 return false;
3589
3590 length--;
3591 integer /= 10;
3592 }
3593
3594 return length == 0;
3595}
3596
3597#ifdef __GNUC__
3598__attribute__((pure))
3599#endif
3600static inline bool equals(unsigned long long integer, const char *s) {
3601 if (integer == ULLONG_MAX)
3602 return strcmp(s, "18446744073709551615") == 0;
3603
3604 if (integer == 0ULL)
3605 return strcmp(s, "0") == 0;
3606
3607 size_t length = strlen(s);
3608
3609 if (length == 0)
3610 return false;
3611
3612 while (integer > 0) {
3613 int digit = int(integer % 10);
3614
3615 if (s[length - 1] != '0' + digit)
3616 return false;
3617
3618 length--;
3619 integer /= 10;
3620 }
3621
3622 return length == 0;
3623}

3625static inline double stringToDouble(InStream &in, const char *buffer) {
3626 double result;
3627
3628 size_t length = strlen(buffer);
3629
3630 int minusCount = 0;
3631 int plusCount = 0;
3632 int decimalPointCount = 0;
3633 int digitCount = 0;
3634 int eCount = 0;
3635
3636 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
3637 if (('0' <= buffer[i] && buffer[i] <= '9') || buffer[i] == '.'
3638 || buffer[i] == 'e' || buffer[i] == 'E'
3639 || buffer[i] == '-' || buffer[i] == '+') {
3640 if ('0' <= buffer[i] && buffer[i] <= '9')
3641 digitCount++;
3642 if (buffer[i] == 'e' || buffer[i] == 'E')
3643 eCount++;
3644 if (buffer[i] == '-')
3645 minusCount++;
3646 if (buffer[i] == '+')
3647 plusCount++;
3648 if (buffer[i] == '.')
3649 decimalPointCount++;
3650 } else
3651 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3652 }
3653
3654 // If for sure is not a number in standard notation or in e-notation.
3655 if (digitCount == 0 || minusCount > 2 || plusCount > 2 || decimalPointCount > 1 || eCount > 1)
3656 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3657
3658 char *suffix = new char[length + 1];
3659 std::memset(suffix, 0, length + 1);
3660 int scanned = std::sscanf(buffer, "%lf%s", &result, suffix);
3661 bool empty = strlen(suffix) == 0;
3662 delete[] suffix;
3663
3664 if (scanned == 1 || (scanned == 2 && empty)) {
3665 if (__testlib_isNaN(result))
3666 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3667 return result;
3668 } else
3669 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3670}
3671
3672static inline double stringToDouble(InStream &in, const std::string& buffer) {
3673 for (size_t i = 0; i < buffer.length(); i++)
3674 if (buffer[i] == '\0')
3675 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found (it contains \\0)").c_str());
3676 return stringToDouble(in, buffer.c_str());
3677}
3678
3679static inline double stringToStrictDouble(InStream &in, const char *buffer,
3680 int minAfterPointDigitCount, int maxAfterPointDigitCount) {
3681 if (minAfterPointDigitCount < 0)
3682 in.quit(_fail, "stringToStrictDouble: minAfterPointDigitCount should be non-negative.");
3683
3684 if (minAfterPointDigitCount > maxAfterPointDigitCount)
3685 in.quit(_fail,
3686 "stringToStrictDouble: minAfterPointDigitCount should be less or equal to maxAfterPointDigitCount.");
3687
3688 double result;
3689
3690 size_t length = strlen(buffer);
3691
3692 if (length == 0 || length > 1000)
3693 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3694
3695 if (buffer[0] != '-' && (buffer[0] < '0' || buffer[0] > '9'))
3696 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3697
3698 int pointPos = -1;
3699 for (size_t i = 1; i + 1 < length; i++) {
3700 if (buffer[i] == '.') {
3701 if (pointPos > -1)
3702 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3703 pointPos = int(i);
3704 }
3705 if (buffer[i] != '.' && (buffer[i] < '0' || buffer[i] > '9'))
3706 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3707 }
3708
3709 if (buffer[length - 1] < '0' || buffer[length - 1] > '9')
3710 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3711
3712 int afterDigitsCount = (pointPos == -1 ? 0 : int(length) - pointPos - 1);
3713 if (afterDigitsCount < minAfterPointDigitCount || afterDigitsCount > maxAfterPointDigitCount)
3714 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double with number of digits after point in range ["
3715 + vtos(minAfterPointDigitCount)
3716 + ","
3717 + vtos(maxAfterPointDigitCount)
3718 + "], but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str()
3719 );
3720
3721 int firstDigitPos = -1;
3722 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++)
3723 if (buffer[i] >= '0' && buffer[i] <= '9') {
3724 firstDigitPos = int(i);
3725 break;
3726 }
3727
3728 if (firstDigitPos > 1 || firstDigitPos == -1)
3729 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3730
3731 if (buffer[firstDigitPos] == '0' && firstDigitPos + 1 < int(length)
3732 && buffer[firstDigitPos + 1] >= '0' && buffer[firstDigitPos + 1] <= '9')
3733 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected strict double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3734
3735 char *suffix = new char[length + 1];
3736 std::memset(suffix, 0, length + 1);
3737 int scanned = std::sscanf(buffer, "%lf%s", &result, suffix);
3738 bool empty = strlen(suffix) == 0;
3739 delete[] suffix;
3740
3741 if (scanned == 1 || (scanned == 2 && empty)) {
3742 if (__testlib_isNaN(result) || __testlib_isInfinite(result))
3743 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3744 if (buffer[0] == '-' && result >= 0)
3745 in.quit(_pe, ("Redundant minus in \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3746 return result;
3747 } else
3748 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3749}
3750
3751static inline double stringToStrictDouble(InStream &in, const std::string& buffer,
3752 int minAfterPointDigitCount, int maxAfterPointDigitCount) {
3753 for (size_t i = 0; i < buffer.length(); i++)
3754 if (buffer[i] == '\0')
3755 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected double, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found (it contains \\0)").c_str());
3756 return stringToStrictDouble(in, buffer.c_str(), minAfterPointDigitCount, maxAfterPointDigitCount);
3757}

3759static inline long long stringToLongLong(InStream &in, const char *buffer) {
3760 size_t length = strlen(buffer);
3761 if (length == 0 || length > 20)
3762 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected integer, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3763
3764 bool has_minus = (length > 1 && buffer[0] == '-');
3765 int zeroes = 0;
3766 bool processingZeroes = true;
3767
3768 for (int i = (has_minus ? 1 : 0); i < int(length); i++) {
3769 if (buffer[i] == '0' && processingZeroes)
3770 zeroes++;
3771 else
3772 processingZeroes = false;
3773
3774 if (buffer[i] < '0' || buffer[i] > '9')
3775 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected integer, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3776 }
3777
3778 long long int result;
3779 try {
3780 result = std::stoll(buffer);
3781 } catch (const std::exception&) {
3782 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected integer, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3783 } catch (...) {
3784 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected integer, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3785 }
3786
3787 if ((zeroes > 0 && (result != 0 || has_minus)) || zeroes > 1)
3788 in.quit(_pe, ("Expected integer, but \"" + __testlib_part(buffer) + "\" found").c_str());
3789
3790 return result;
3791}

3795 if (buffer[i] == '\0')

3797 return stringToLongLong(in, buffer.c_str());
3798}

4026double InStream::readReal(double minv, double maxv, const std::string &variableName) {
4027 double result = readReal();
4028
4029 if (result < minv || result > maxv) {
4030 if (readManyIteration == NO_INDEX) {
4031 if (variableName.empty())
4032 quit(_wa, ("Double " + vtos(result) + " violates the range [" + vtos(minv) + ", " + vtos(maxv) +
4033 "]").c_str());
4034 else
4035 quit(_wa, ("Double parameter [name=" + std::string(variableName) + "] equals to " + vtos(result) +
4036 ", violates the range [" + vtos(minv) + ", " + vtos(maxv) + "]").c_str());
4037 } else {
4038 if (variableName.empty())
4039 quit(_wa, ("Double element [index=" + vtos(readManyIteration) + "] equals to " + vtos(result) +
4040 ", violates the range [" + vtos(minv) + ", " + vtos(maxv) + "]").c_str());
4041 else
4042 quit(_wa,
4043 ("Double element " + std::string(variableName) + "[" + vtos(readManyIteration) + "] equals to " +
4044 vtos(result) + ", violates the range [" + vtos(minv) + ", " + vtos(maxv) + "]").c_str());
4045 }
4046 }
4047
4048 if (strict && !variableName.empty()) {
4049 validator.addBoundsHit(variableName, ValidatorBoundsHit(
4050 doubleDelta(minv, result) < ValidatorBoundsHit::EPS,
4051 doubleDelta(maxv, result) < ValidatorBoundsHit::EPS
4052 ));
4053 validator.adjustConstantBounds(variableName, minv, maxv);
4054 validator.addVariable(variableName);
4055 }
4056
4057 return result;
4058}

4167
4168bool InStream::eoln() {
4169 if (!strict && NULL == reader)
4170 return true;
4171
4172 int c = reader->nextChar();
4173
4174 if (!strict) {
4175 if (c == EOFC)
4176 return true;
4177
4178 if (c == CR) {
4179 c = reader->nextChar();
4180
4181 if (c != LF) {
4182 reader->unreadChar(c);
4183 reader->unreadChar(CR);
4184 return false;
4185 } else
4186 return true;
4187 }
4188
4189 if (c == LF)
4190 return true;
4191
4192 reader->unreadChar(c);
4193 return false;
4194 } else {
4195 bool returnCr = false;
4196
4197#if (defined(ON_WINDOWS) && !defined(FOR_LINUX)) || defined(FOR_WINDOWS)
4198 if (c != CR) {
4199 reader->unreadChar(c);
4200 return false;
4201 } else {
4202 if (!returnCr)
4203 returnCr = true;
4204 c = reader->nextChar();
4205 }
4206#endif
4207 if (c != LF) {
4208 reader->unreadChar(c);
4209 if (returnCr)
4210 reader->unreadChar(CR);
4211 return false;
4212 }
4213
4214 return true;
4215 }
4216}

4233bool InStream::seekEoln() {
4234 if (!strict && NULL == reader)
4235 return true;
4236
4237 int cur;

4239 cur = reader->nextChar();

4243 return eoln();

4250void InStream::readStringTo(std::string &result) {
4251 if (NULL == reader)
4252 quit(_pe, "Expected line");
4253
4254 result.clear();
4255
4256 for (;;) {
4257 int cur = reader->curChar();
4258
4259 if (cur == LF || cur == EOFC)
4260 break;
4261
4262 if (cur == CR) {
4263 cur = reader->nextChar();
4264 if (reader->curChar() == LF) {
4265 reader->unreadChar(cur);
4266 break;
4267 }
4268 }
4269
4270 lastLine = reader->getLine();
4271 result += char(reader->nextChar());
4272 }
4273
4274 if (strict)
4275 readEoln();
4276 else
4277 eoln();
4278}

4518static void __testlib_ensuresPreconditions() {

4520 __TESTLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(int) == 4);
4521
4522 // testlib assumes: INT_MAX == 2147483647.
4523 __TESTLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(INT_MAX == 2147483647);
4524
4525 // testlib assumes: sizeof(long long) = 8.
4526 __TESTLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(long long) == 8);
4527
4528 // testlib assumes: sizeof(double) = 8.
4529 __TESTLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(double) == 8);
4530
4531 // testlib assumes: no -ffast-math.
4532 if (!__testlib_isNaN(+__testlib_nan()))
4533 quit(_fail, "Function __testlib_isNaN is not working correctly: possible reason is '-ffast-math'");
4534 if (!__testlib_isNaN(-__testlib_nan()))

4935/*
4936 * Do not use random_shuffle, because it will produce different result
4937 * for different C++ compilers.
4938 *
4939 * This implementation uses testlib random_t to produce random numbers, so
4940 * it is stable.
4941 */
4942template<typename _RandomAccessIter>
4943void shuffle(_RandomAccessIter __first, _RandomAccessIter __last) {
4944 if (__first == __last) return;
4945 for (_RandomAccessIter __i = __first + 1; __i != __last; ++__i)
4946 std::iter_swap(__i, __first + rnd.next(int(__i - __first) + 1));
4947}

5451size_t getOptType(char *s) {
5452 if (!s || strlen(s) <= 1)
5453 return 0;
5454
5455 if (s[0] == '-') {
5456 if (isalpha(s[1]))
5457 return 1;
5458 else if (s[1] == '-')
5459 return isalpha(s[2]) ? 2 : 0;
5460 }
5461
5462 return 0;
5463}
5464
5494size_t parseOpt(size_t argc, char *argv[], size_t index, std::map<std::string, TestlibOpt> &opts) {
5495 if (index >= argc)
5496 return 0;
5497
5498 size_t type = getOptType(argv[index]), inc = 1;
5499 if (type > 0) {
5500 std::string key(argv[index] + type), val;
5501 size_t sep = key.find('=');
5502 if (sep != std::string::npos) {
5503 val = key.substr(sep + 1);
5504 key = key.substr(0, sep);
5505 } else {
5506 if (index + 1 < argc && getOptType(argv[index + 1]) == 0) {
5507 val = argv[index + 1];
5508 inc = 2;
5509 } else {
5510 if (key.length() > 1 && isdigit(key[1])) {
5511 val = key.substr(1);
5512 key = key.substr(0, 1);
5513 } else {
5514 val = "true";
5515 }
5516 }
5517 }
5518 opts[key].value = val;
5519 } else {
5520 return inc;
5521 }
5522
5523 return inc;
5524}

5555void prepareOpts(int argc, char *argv[]) {
5556 if (argc <= 0)
5557 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected argc>=0 but found " + toString(argc));
5558 size_t n = static_cast<size_t>(argc); // NOLINT(hicpp-use-auto,modernize-use-auto)
5559 __testlib_opts = std::map<std::string, TestlibOpt>();
5560 for (size_t index = 1; index < n; index += parseOpt(n, argv, index, __testlib_opts));
5561 __testlib_argv = std::vector<std::string>(n);
5562 for (size_t index = 0; index < n; index++)
5563 __testlib_argv[index] = argv[index];
5564}

5572 __testlib_fail("Opts: index '" + toString(index) + "' is out of range [0,"
5573 + toString(__testlib_argv.size()) + ")");
5574 return __testlib_argv[size_t(index)];
5575}

5594std::string parseExponentialOptValue(const std::string &s) {
5595 size_t pos = std::string::npos;
5596 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
5597 if (s[i] == 'e' || s[i] == 'E') {
5598 if (pos != std::string::npos)
5599 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected typical exponential notation but '" + compress(s) + "' found");
5600 pos = i;
5601 }
5602 if (pos == std::string::npos)
5603 return s;
5604 std::string e = s.substr(pos + 1);
5605 if (!e.empty() && e[0] == '+')
5606 e = e.substr(1);
5607 if (e.empty())
5608 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected typical exponential notation but '" + compress(s) + "' found");
5609 if (e.length() > 20)
5610 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected typical exponential notation but '" + compress(s) + "' found");
5611 int ne = optValueToIntegral<int>(e, false);
5612 std::string num = s.substr(0, pos);
5613 if (num.length() > 20)
5614 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected typical exponential notation but '" + compress(s) + "' found");
5615 if (!num.empty() && num[0] == '+')
5616 num = num.substr(1);
5617 optValueToLongDouble(num);
5618 bool minus = false;
5619 if (num[0] == '-') {
5620 minus = true;
5621 num = num.substr(1);
5622 }
5623 for (int i = 0; i < +ne; i++) {
5624 size_t sep = num.find('.');
5625 if (sep == std::string::npos)
5626 num += '0';
5627 else {
5628 if (sep + 1 == num.length())
5629 num[sep] = '0';
5630 else
5631 std::swap(num[sep], num[sep + 1]);
5632 }
5633 }
5634 for (int i = 0; i < -ne; i++) {
5635 size_t sep = num.find('.');
5636 if (sep == std::string::npos)
5637 num.insert(num.begin() + int(num.length()) - 1, '.');
5638 else {
5639 if (sep == 0)
5640 num.insert(num.begin() + 1, '0');
5641 else
5642 std::swap(num[sep - 1], num[sep]);
5643 }
5644 }
5645 while (!num.empty() && num[0] == '0')
5646 num = num.substr(1);
5647 while (num.find('.') != std::string::npos && num.back() == '0')
5648 num = num.substr(0, num.length() - 1);
5649 if (!num.empty() && num.back() == '.')
5650 num = num.substr(0, num.length() - 1);
5651 if ((!num.empty() && num[0] == '.') || num.empty())
5652 num.insert(num.begin(), '0');
5653 return (minus ? "-" : "") + num;
5654}
5655
5656template<typename T>
5657T optValueToIntegral(const std::string &s_, bool nonnegative) {
5658 std::string s(parseExponentialOptValue(s_));
5659 if (s.empty())
5660 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected integer but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5661 T value = 0;
5662 long double about = 0.0;
5663 signed char sign = +1;
5664 size_t pos = 0;
5665 if (s[pos] == '-') {
5666 if (nonnegative)
5667 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected non-negative integer but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5668 sign = -1;
5669 pos++;
5670 }
5671 for (size_t i = pos; i < s.length(); i++) {
5672 if (s[i] < '0' || s[i] > '9')
5673 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected integer but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5674 value = T(value * 10 + s[i] - '0');
5675 about = about * 10 + s[i] - '0';
5676 }
5677 value *= sign;
5678 about *= sign;
5679 if (fabsl(value - about) > 0.1)
5680 __testlib_fail("Opts: integer overflow: expected integer but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5681 return value;
5682}
5683
5684long double optValueToLongDouble(const std::string &s_) {
5685 std::string s(parseExponentialOptValue(s_));
5686 if (s.empty())
5687 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected float number but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5688 long double value = 0.0;
5689 signed char sign = +1;
5690 size_t pos = 0;
5691 if (s[pos] == '-') {
5692 sign = -1;
5693 pos++;
5694 }
5695 bool period = false;
5696 long double mul = 1.0;
5697 for (size_t i = pos; i < s.length(); i++) {
5698 if (s[i] == '.') {
5699 if (period)
5700 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected float number but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5701 else {
5702 period = true;
5703 continue;
5704 }
5705 }
5706 if (period)
5707 mul *= 10.0;
5708 if (s[i] < '0' || s[i] > '9')
5709 __testlib_fail("Opts: expected float number but '" + compress(s_) + "' found");
5710 if (period)
5711 value += (s[i] - '0') / mul;
5712 else
5713 value = value * 10 + s[i] - '0';
5714 }
5715 value *= sign;
5716 return value;
5717}

5731/* About the following part for opt with 2 and 3 arguments.
5732 *
5733 * To parse the argv/opts correctly for a give type (integer, floating point or
5734 * string), some meta programming must be done to determine the type of
5735 * the type, and use the correct parsing function accordingly.
5736 *
5737 * The pseudo algorithm for determining the type of T and parse it accordingly
5738 * is as follows:
5739 *
5740 * if (T is integral type) {
5741 * if (T is unsigned) {
5742 * parse the argv/opt as an **unsigned integer** of type T.
5743 * } else {
5744 * parse the argv/opt as an **signed integer** of type T.
5745 * } else {
5746 * if (T is floating point type) {
5747 * parse the argv/opt as an **floating point** of type T.
5748 * } else {
5749 * // T should be std::string
5750 * just the raw content of the argv/opts.
5751 * }
5752 * }
5753 *
5754 * To help with meta programming, some `opt` function with 2 or 3 arguments are
5755 * defined.
5756 *
5757 * Opt with 3 arguments: T opt(true/false is_integral, true/false is_unsigned, index/key)
5758 *
5759 * + The first argument is for determining whether the type T is an integral
5760 * type. That is, the result of std::is_integral<T>() should be passed to
5761 * this argument. When false, the type _should_ be either floating point or a
5762 * std::string.
5763 *
5764 * + The second argument is for determining whether the signedness of the type
5765 * T (if it is unsigned or signed). That is, the result of
5766 * std::is_unsigned<T>() should be passed to this argument. This argument can
5767 * be ignored if the first one is false, because it only applies to integer.
5768 *
5769 * Opt with 2 arguments: T opt(true/false is_floating_point, index/key)
5770 * + The first argument is for determining whether the type T is a floating
5771 * point type. That is, the result of std::is_floating_point<T>() should be
5772 * passed to this argument. When false, the type _should_ be a std::string.
5773 */
5774
5775template<typename T>
5776T opt(std::false_type is_floating_point, int index);
5777
5778template<>
5779std::string opt(std::false_type /*is_floating_point*/, int index) {
5780 return __testlib_indexToArgv(index);
5781}

5783template<typename T>
5784T opt(std::true_type /*is_floating_point*/, int index) {
5785 return T(optValueToLongDouble(__testlib_indexToArgv(index)));
5786}

5907enum TestResultVerdict {
5908 SKIPPED,
5909 OK,
5910 WRONG_ANSWER,
5911 RUNTIME_ERROR,
5912 TIME_LIMIT_EXCEEDED,
5913 IDLENESS_LIMIT_EXCEEDED,
5914 MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED,
5915 COMPILATION_ERROR,
5916 CRASHED,
5917 FAILED
5918};
5919
5920std::string serializeVerdict(TestResultVerdict verdict) {
5921 switch (verdict) {
5922 case SKIPPED: return "SKIPPED";
5923 case OK: return "OK";
5924 case WRONG_ANSWER: return "WRONG_ANSWER";
5925 case RUNTIME_ERROR: return "RUNTIME_ERROR";
5926 case TIME_LIMIT_EXCEEDED: return "TIME_LIMIT_EXCEEDED";
5927 case IDLENESS_LIMIT_EXCEEDED: return "IDLENESS_LIMIT_EXCEEDED";
5928 case MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED: return "MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED";
5929 case COMPILATION_ERROR: return "COMPILATION_ERROR";
5930 case CRASHED: return "CRASHED";
5931 case FAILED: return "FAILED";
5932 }
5933 throw "Unexpected verdict";
5934}
5935
5936TestResultVerdict deserializeTestResultVerdict(std::string s) {
5937 if (s == "SKIPPED")
5938 return SKIPPED;
5939 else if (s == "OK")
5940 return OK;
5941 else if (s == "WRONG_ANSWER")
5942 return WRONG_ANSWER;
5943 else if (s == "RUNTIME_ERROR")
5944 return RUNTIME_ERROR;
5945 else if (s == "TIME_LIMIT_EXCEEDED")
5946 return TIME_LIMIT_EXCEEDED;
5947 else if (s == "IDLENESS_LIMIT_EXCEEDED")
5948 return IDLENESS_LIMIT_EXCEEDED;
5949 else if (s == "MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED")
5950 return MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED;
5951 else if (s == "COMPILATION_ERROR")
5952 return COMPILATION_ERROR;
5953 else if (s == "CRASHED")
5954 return CRASHED;
5955 else if (s == "FAILED")
5956 return FAILED;
5957 ensuref(false, "Unexpected serialized TestResultVerdict");
5958 // No return actually.
5959 return FAILED;
5960}

5977std::string serializePoints(double points) {
5978 if (std::isnan(points))
5979 return "";
5980 else {
5981 char c[64];
5982 snprintf(c, 64, "%.03lf", points);
5983 return c;
5984 }
5985}
5986
5987double deserializePoints(std::string s) {
5988 if (s.empty())
5989 return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
5990 else {
5991 double result;
5992 ensuref(sscanf(s.c_str(), "%lf", &result) == 1, "Invalid serialized points");
5993 return result;
5994 }
5995}
5996
5997std::string escapeTestResultString(std::string s) {
5998 std::string result;
5999 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
6000 if (s[i] == '\r')
6001 continue;
6002 if (s[i] == '\n') {
6003 result += "\\n";
6004 continue;
6005 }
6006 if (s[i] == '\\' || s[i] == ';')
6007 result += '\\';
6008 result += s[i];
6009 }
6010 return result;
6011}
6012
6013std::string unescapeTestResultString(std::string s) {
6014 std::string result;
6015 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
6016 if (s[i] == '\\' && i + 1 < s.length()) {
6017 if (s[i + 1] == 'n') {
6018 result += '\n';
6019 i++;
6020 continue;
6021 } else if (s[i + 1] == ';' || s[i + 1] == '\\') {
6022 result += s[i + 1];
6023 i++;
6024 continue;
6025 }
6026 }
6027 result += s[i];
6028 }
6029 return result;
6030}
6031
6032std::string serializeTestResult(TestResult tr) {
6033 std::string result;
6034 result += std::to_string(tr.testIndex);
6035 result += ";";
6036 result += escapeTestResultString(tr.testset);
6037 result += ";";
6038 result += escapeTestResultString(tr.group);
6039 result += ";";
6040 result += serializeVerdict(tr.verdict);
6041 result += ";";
6042 result += serializePoints(tr.points);
6043 result += ";";
6044 result += std::to_string(tr.timeConsumed);
6045 result += ";";
6046 result += std::to_string(tr.memoryConsumed);
6047 result += ";";
6048 result += escapeTestResultString(tr.input);
6049 result += ";";
6050 result += escapeTestResultString(tr.output);
6051 result += ";";
6052 result += escapeTestResultString(tr.answer);

6060TestResult deserializeTestResult(std::string s) {
6061 std::vector<std::string> items;
6062 std::string t;
6063 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
6064 if (s[i] == '\\') {
6065 t += s[i];
6066 if (i + 1 < s.length())
6067 t += s[i + 1];
6068 i++;
6069 continue;
6070 } else {
6071 if (s[i] == ';') {
6072 items.push_back(t);
6073 t = "";
6074 } else
6075 t += s[i];
6076 }
6077 }
6078 items.push_back(t);
6079
6080 ensuref(items.size() == 12, "Invalid TestResult serialization: expected exactly 12 items");
6081
6082 TestResult tr;
6083 size_t pos = 0;
6084 tr.testIndex = stoi(items[pos++]);
6085 tr.testset = unescapeTestResultString(items[pos++]);
6086 tr.group = unescapeTestResultString(items[pos++]);
6087 tr.verdict = deserializeTestResultVerdict(items[pos++]);
6088 tr.points = deserializePoints(items[pos++]);
6089 tr.timeConsumed = stoll(items[pos++]);
6090 tr.memoryConsumed = stoll(items[pos++]);
6091 tr.input = unescapeTestResultString(items[pos++]);
6092 tr.output = unescapeTestResultString(items[pos++]);
6093 tr.answer = unescapeTestResultString(items[pos++]);
6094 tr.exitCode = stoi(items[pos++]);
6095 tr.checkerComment = unescapeTestResultString(items[pos++]);
6096
6097 return tr;
6098}

6100std::vector<TestResult> readTestResults(std::string fileName) {
6101 std::ifstream stream;
6102 stream.open(fileName.c_str(), std::ios::in);
6103 ensuref(stream.is_open(), "Can't read test results file '%s'", fileName.c_str());

6107 if (!line.empty())
6108 result.push_back(deserializeTestResult(line));

6110 return result;
